= Do We Revive Andropov's Anti-Alcohol Campaign?

Growing popularity for the prohibition of alcohol has been indicated in recent surveys, especially among women, and we have been advised to enact a revival of the Andropov era anti-drunkenness campaign. This is due to increasing mortality related to excess drinking as well as the hefty costs associated with alcoholism (ie, lack of worker productivity, higher criminality, domestic violence, etc.).

