@harsh_crackdowns
title: Institute Harsh Crackdowns
on-arrival: budget -= 3; reformer_approval += 2; moderate_approval += 1; hardliner_approval -= 2; popular_approval -= 4; separatism += 2

We experience a dip in popularity across the board (in Politburo and among the general public) and the economy will suffer with less money coming in from liquor sales, which account for one third of the GDP. Though drunkenness, and costs associated with it, will decrease, this will not be enough to offset the damage done to the budget and Gorbachev's popularity.

@partial_crackdown
title: A Partial Crackdown
on-arrival: budget -= 2; reformer_approval += 1; moderate_approval += 2; hardliner_approval -= 1; popular_approval -= 2; separatism += 1

We take a moderate position, institute severe police crackdowns on public drunkenness and increase punishment for crimes committed while drunk. This will boost Gorbachev's support within the party, but only mildly. Additionally, income from alcohol sales decrease slightly as less people are day drinking.

@do_not_revive
title: Do not Revive the Campaign
on-arrival: revive_andrapov_campaign = 0; reformer_approval -= 2; hardliner_approval += 2; popular_approval -= 1;

We do not revive the Anti-Alcohol campaign. As such, disapproval among the Politburo increases as it does among citizens who see alcoholism as a problem. However, on a positive note, we suffer no budget shortfall.

@provide_more_funding
title: Provide More Funding to the Alcohol Industry.
on-arrival: budget += 3; reformer_approval -= 3; moderate_approval -= 1; hardliner_approval -= 1; popular_approval += 2; separatism -= 1

To a great degree of controversy, we decide that the revenue from the alcohol tax is too enticing to pass up. We invest further into the alcohol industry by subsidizing vineyards and
distilleries, aiming to maximize the returns on an already substantive industry. While our budget increases, drunkenness and the problems associated with it worsen.




